
[1]fiction

   FIC'TION, n. [L. fictio, from fingo, to feign.]

   1. The act of feigning, inventing or imagining; as, by the mere fiction
   of the mind.

   2. That which is feigned, invented or imagined. The story is a fiction.

   So also was the fiction of those golden apples kept by a dragon, taken
   from the serpent which tempted Eve.
